---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - Hampstead Architects & Interiors"
  description="The story of London's first architectural concierge service, connecting discerning clients with the city's finest design specialists since our founding in Hampstead."
  schemaType="AboutPage"
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-warm-stone">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-serif font-light mb-6">
        The Private Office for<br>Architectural Discernment
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-light text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        We don't design buildings. We design the process of finding the architect who will design your building perfectly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founding Story -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="grid-editorial">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8 lg:col-start-3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-8">The Origin</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Hampstead Architects & Interiors was born from a problem we encountered repeatedly at <strong>Hampstead Renovations Group</strong>, our construction arm.
          </p>

          <p>
            Clients would arrive with beautiful drawings from talented architects‚Äîdrawings that were structurally impossible, planning-doomed, or budget-catastrophic. The architect specialized in minimalist new-builds, but the client needed a heritage restoration specialist. Or the design was exquisite but assumed unlimited funds.
          </p>

          <p>
            We found ourselves acting as mediators: "This won't pass Camden Conservation. Your party wall surveyor will reject this. The Listed Building Consent officer will laugh at this proposal."
          </p>

          <p class="text-xl text-charcoal/90 font-light italic border-l-3 border-oxidized-copper pl-6">
            The mismatch between client needs and architect specialization was costing everyone‚Äîtime, money, and emotional energy.
          </p>

          <p>
            So in 2018, we formalized what we'd been doing informally: <strong>architectural curation</strong>.
          </p>

          <p>
            We leveraged our 15 years of construction relationships to build a network of London's finest specialist studios‚Äîeach vetted not just for design talent, but for delivery reliability, planning pragmatism, and client empathy.
          </p>

          <p>
            Today, <strong>Hampstead Architects & Interiors</strong> operates from Palace Court on Finchley Road as an independent concierge service, affiliated with but distinct from the construction business. We match, we curate, we oversee‚Äîbut we never impose a singular style.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Connection to Renovations Group -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-warm-stone">
    <div class="grid-editorial">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-10 lg:col-start-2">
        <div class="bg-white/50 border border-charcoal/10 p-8 md:p-12">
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif font-light mb-6 text-oxidized-copper">
            Our Unique Advantage: Design + Build Synergy
          </h3>

          <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Unlike standalone architectural practices, we have <strong>Hampstead Renovations Group</strong> in our DNA. This means:
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
              <div class="bg-white p-6 border border-charcoal/10">
                <h4 class="font-medium text-oxidized-copper mb-3">Buildability Assurance</h4>
                <p class="text-base">
                  Every design concept is reviewed by our construction team <em>before</em> you see it. No fantasy drawings that cost double to build.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white p-6 border border-charcoal/10">
                <h4 class="font-medium text-oxidized-copper mb-3">Cost Certainty</h4>
                <p class="text-base">
                  We provide accurate cost guidance from Day 1. If your architect proposes handmade Moroccan zellige, we know the real price‚Äînot the optimistic estimate.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white p-6 border border-charcoal/10">
                <h4 class="font-medium text-oxidized-copper mb-3">Seamless Delivery</h4>
                <p class="text-base">
                  If you choose Hampstead Renovations as your contractor, there's zero friction between design and execution. We speak both languages.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white p-6 border border-charcoal/10">
                <h4 class="font-medium text-oxidized-copper mb-3">Client Advocacy</h4>
                <p class="text-base">
                  We remain your ally throughout. If the architect's vision drifts from your brief, we intervene. If the contractor cuts corners, we hold them accountable.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 italic">
              <strong>Independence Note:</strong> You are never obligated to use Hampstead Renovations Group as your contractor. We present competitive bids alongside 2-3 other vetted builders. Choice is always yours.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Approach -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="grid-editorial">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8 lg:col-start-3">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-8">How We Work</h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">We Are Curators, Not Gatekeepers</h3>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              Our role is to expand your access to talent, not restrict it. We introduce you to architects you'd never find on Google‚Äîspecialists who don't advertise because they work exclusively through referrals.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">We Speak Planning</h3>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              15 years in Hampstead, Belsize Park, and Primrose Hill means we know Camden Planning better than most architects. We know which officers favor contemporary insertions in conservation areas, which ones demand brick-for-brick matching, and how to navigate Article 4 Direction constraints.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">We Protect Your Investment</h3>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              Every architect in our network carries ¬£2 million+ professional indemnity insurance, maintains RIBA Chartered status (or equivalent), and has passed our financial stability checks. We eliminate risk before you ever meet them.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4 text-oxidized-copper">We Value Confidentiality</h3>
            <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
              Your project details, budget, and identity are never shared publicly. Architects in our network sign NDAs. Case studies are published with client anonymity unless you explicitly authorize otherwise.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Team Narrative -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-charcoal text-cream">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-8 text-center">The Studio</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Our team at Palace Court combines architectural training, construction experience, and planning expertise. We're not designers ourselves‚Äîwe're <strong>design facilitators</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          Think of us as the art dealer who knows every gallery in London, understands your taste better than you do, and negotiates on your behalf. Except instead of paintings, we're curating the architect who will design the most expensive purchase of your life.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mt-12">
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 bg-warm-stone rounded-full"></div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-xl mb-2">Simon Hargreaves</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-cream/70 mb-3">Founding Director</p>
            <p class="text-sm">
              Former project architect at Foster + Partners. 20 years navigating Camden Planning. RIBA conservation specialist.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 bg-warm-stone rounded-full"></div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-xl mb-2">Eleanor Chen</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-cream/70 mb-3">Interior Design Director</p>
            <p class="text-sm">
              Ex-Soho House Design Studio. Specialist in FF&E procurement from Italian luxury manufacturers. Fluent in material alchemy.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 bg-warm-stone rounded-full"></div>
            <h3 class="font-medium text-xl mb-2">Marcus Okonkwo</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-cream/70 mb-3">Technical Director</p>
            <p class="text-sm">
              Chartered structural engineer. Party Wall Act guru. Has resolved 200+ basement excavation disputes without litigation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-sm text-cream/60 italic text-center mt-12">
          Team profile photography is placeholder. Professional headshots are scheduled as part of our website completion phase.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Awards & Recognition Placeholder -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-8 text-center">Recognition & Affiliations</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="text-center p-8 bg-warm-stone border border-charcoal/10">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 mx-auto mb-4 bg-white/50 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-3xl text-charcoal/30">üèõÔ∏è</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-lg mb-2">RIBA Affiliated</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
            All network architects are RIBA Chartered Practices or equivalent professional status.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center p-8 bg-warm-stone border border-charcoal/10">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 mx-auto mb-4 bg-white/50 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-3xl text-charcoal/30">üèÜ</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-lg mb-2">Award-Winning Network</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
            Our partner studios have won Camden Design Awards, RIBA Regional Awards, and Civic Trust commendations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center p-8 bg-warm-stone border border-charcoal/10">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 mx-auto mb-4 bg-white/50 flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-3xl text-charcoal/30">üì∞</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-medium text-lg mb-2">Press Coverage</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70">
            Featured in Architectural Digest, Telegraph Property, and The Modern House editorial content.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-sm text-charcoal/60 italic mt-8">
        Detailed awards page with certifications, press clippings, and accolades is scheduled for Phase 3 content expansion.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Hampstead -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-oxidized-copper text-cream">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-6">Why Hampstead?</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Hampstead isn't just our address‚Äîit's our laboratory. This is where <strong>heritage conservation meets contemporary aspiration</strong>, where planning restrictions are strictest, where basements cost ¬£10,000 per cubic meter, and where clients expect museum-quality interiors.
        </p>

        <p>
          If you can navigate Hampstead's Grade II listed terraces, Article 4 directions, and conservation area constraints, you can handle any architectural challenge in London.
        </p>

        <p class="text-xl font-light italic">
          We learned the hard way‚Äîthrough 15 years of party wall disputes, planning appeals, and structural engineer standoffs‚Äîso you don't have to.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Call to Action -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-light mb-6">
        Start with a Conversation
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        No sales pitch. No obligation. Just a candid discussion about your project, the constraints you'll face, and whether our curator model is the right fit.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-oxidized-copper text-cream font-medium tracking-wide hover:bg-charcoal transition-colors"
      >
        Book Your Briefing at Palace Court
      </a>
      <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/60 mt-4">
        Palace Court, 250 Finchley Road, London NW3 6DN
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .grid-editorial {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .border-l-3 {
    border-left-width: 3px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .grid-editorial > div {
      grid-column: 1 / -1 !important;
    }
  }
</style>
